ell University Library, the Harvard Libraries, the Library of Congress and possibly other libraries and at least half-a-dozen months in actual composition, settling down for this purpose at some quiet, secluded, hay-fever-less spot.





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





P.S. I have not applied for a Fulbright or any other award.





